<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,226,665]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<keyLead pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
- Prothoracic hypomera with shallow depression, lacking distinct cavity (
<figureCitation box="[966,1046,573,596]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–46. 42" captionStartId="46.[151,269,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[419,1208,199,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-177@46.[267,1319,150,1624]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 42–46. 42. Lateral view of P. venustus hypomeron. 43. Ventral view of tarsus of P. venustus. 44–46. Male genitalia. 44. P. diabolicus; 45. P. plicatus; 46. P. venustus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5230767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5230767/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
